olive oil
1 packet fusilli
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet diced bacon
1 tomato
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 lemon
1 cucumber

• Boil the kettle. Pour boiling water into a medium saucepan over high heat
with a good pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Drain fusilli, then return to saucepan with chicken style-stock powder and
a drizzle with olive oil. Stir to combine.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes.

• While bacon is cooking, finely chop tomato and cucumber.
• Cut lemon into wedges.

• When you're ready to pack your lunch, stir tomato, cucumber, bacon, dill & parsley mayonnaise, a good squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil through the fusilli. Season to taste.
• Divide between two containers and sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate. Enjoy!

TIP: This pasta salad is best enjoyed cooled!